      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TIGER SHIRL NZ (5) drew a wide gate last start and was safely held, beaten 40 metres into seventh at Albion Park over 1660m. Has the class to take this out. BLING THE NOISE (9) had been racing in fine form then went close again last time over 1660m at Albion Park, finishing second and just a head from the winner. No favours expected from this draw. Meets a comparable field and he can go one better. PISCINA (6) broke last start but still managed to fill a minor placing over 1780m at this track, finishing 17 metres from the winner. That was a pleasing progression after missing the placings the run before. Beautifully placed and is sure to be thereabouts again. UNCUT GEM (7) ended last prep with a seventh at Mildura over 1790m 11 weeks ago. Can open this campaign with a more positive effort.",
